she kept looking outside.

651
00:46:09,600 --> 00:46:11,250
I wondered what it was
and looked outside...

652
00:46:12,640 --> 00:46:14,390
A man was waiting for her?

653
00:46:17,870 --> 00:46:20,840
After our meeting, I saw her
getting into his car clearly.

654
00:46:24,080 --> 00:46:26,340
So I just thought he was
her friend or something.

655
00:46:26,660 --> 00:46:28,530
This was such a controversial case,

656
00:46:28,750 --> 00:46:30,850
and I was curious what
kind of person she was.

657
00:46:31,390 --> 00:46:34,080
But when she came with a man,
so I thought it was strange.

658
00:46:48,310 --> 00:46:49,320
Who do you think he is?

659
00:46:49,580 --> 00:46:52,570
Do you think she had another lover?

660
00:46:54,040 --> 00:46:55,890
I don't think she has any
other family members.

661
00:46:57,690 --> 00:47:00,510
By the way, if Ms. Oh finds out about this,

662
00:47:00,620 --> 00:47:02,100
she'll be so shocked.

663
00:47:02,250 --> 00:47:05,280
Ms. Oh worked really hard on this case.

664
00:47:06,290 --> 00:47:08,620
She went with you to Im Yun Hee's home too.

665
00:47:09,620 --> 00:47:11,790
When you were attacked by
Park Su Myeong by a bat,

666
00:47:11,870 --> 00:47:13,410
she was worried sick about you.

667
00:47:13,640 --> 00:47:15,150
Ms. Oh, are you all right?

668
00:47:15,330 --> 00:47:17,500
What about you? Are you hurt?

669
00:47:17,500 --> 00:47:19,660
Oh, my gosh. It's still bleeding.

670
00:47:19,660 --> 00:47:20,990
Oh, no...

671
00:47:30,190 --> 00:47:31,220
Let's go now.

672
00:47:34,690 --> 00:47:37,860
What? You'll represent
Park Su Myeong at his appeal?

673
00:47:38,060 --> 00:47:40,220
You appointed him as a
witness during the trial,

674
00:47:40,230 --> 00:47:43,660
and you're the one who pointed
him out as the real culprit.

675
00:47:44,120 --> 00:47:45,780
But what do you mean,
there's another culprit?

676
00:47:46,660 --> 00:47:49,090
You want to be Park Su Myeong's attorney?
What is this...

677
00:47:49,790 --> 00:47:52,690
I don't know. I'll pretend I didn't
hear this, so you can leave.

678
00:47:52,730 --> 00:47:54,400
- No, I'll just leave.
- Mr. Yeon.

679
00:47:54,410 --> 00:47:57,230
How could you gamble over
something you're not certain of?

680
00:47:57,980 --> 00:48:01,450
Mr. Kwon. Do you know this is
a violation of your work ethics?

681
00:48:03,980 --> 00:48:06,580
Anyway, I cannot allow this.

682
00:48:07,790 --> 00:48:10,510
I told you clearly not to do it.
That's final.

683
00:48:36,910 --> 00:48:38,610
Goodness. Mr. Kwon is making me...

684
00:48:38,620 --> 00:48:41,010
so anxious, and it's
practically killing me.

685
00:48:41,060 --> 00:48:42,730
I might die out of anxiety.

686
00:48:43,480 --> 00:48:44,800
What if he really...

687
00:48:44,890 --> 00:48:47,250
insists on taking Park Su Myeong's case?

688
00:48:47,850 --> 00:48:49,010
I doubt it.

689
00:48:49,330 --> 00:48:51,420
This is so disturbing.

690
00:48:52,690 --> 00:48:54,650
- I'm back.
- Hello.

691
00:48:54,830 --> 00:48:57,160
Ms. Dan. How did your trial go?

692
00:48:59,370 --> 00:49:01,050
Yes. Of course.

693
00:49:01,730 --> 00:49:05,480
It seems like Ms. Oh is shooting
a drama in front of the court.

694
00:49:05,940 --> 00:49:08,940
I saw a sign that read "Love Hurts"...

695
00:49:09,250 --> 00:49:10,760
on a vehicle near there.

696
00:49:14,390 --> 00:49:15,970
Yes, hello? This is Attorney Dan Moon Hee.

697
00:49:16,190 --> 00:49:18,650
It'll be so fun if we all
visit her filming site.

698
00:49:18,690 --> 00:49:19,900
Shall we go?

699
00:49:20,000 --> 00:49:22,990
Hae Yeong, Mr. Yeon has a lot
on his mind right now...

700
00:49:23,000 --> 00:49:24,060
and he's quite disturbed.

701
00:49:24,060 --> 00:49:26,490
