00:52:27,940 --> 00:52:30,340
I walk by the court like
this from time to time.

763
00:52:31,210 --> 00:52:34,180
I never forget how I first felt
when I decided to become...

764
00:52:34,210 --> 00:52:35,970
a judicial officer that
would fight for the weak.

765
00:52:36,250 --> 00:52:38,480
Today seemed like that sort of day.

766
00:52:38,480 --> 00:52:42,030
- Today was that sort of day?
- Yes, let's say it was.

767
00:52:42,250 --> 00:52:45,090
Anyway, I'm glad.
My shoot has been delayed,

768
00:52:45,100 --> 00:52:47,630
and I have some time.
You didn't have lunch yet, right?

769
00:52:47,640 --> 00:52:49,250
Shall we have lunch together?

770
00:52:55,940 --> 00:52:58,900
Why are you all looking at me
instead of eating your food?

771
00:52:59,080 --> 00:53:00,390
This feels so cool.

772
00:53:00,480 --> 00:53:02,970
It feels like I'm eating with
a celebrity all of a sudden.

773
00:53:04,020 --> 00:53:06,810
I felt the same way when I saw
you at the film site earlier.

774
00:53:07,120 --> 00:53:09,240
It made me realize that you're an actress.

775
00:53:09,290 --> 00:53:13,020
I can't believe we used to
hang out and chat with each other.

776
00:53:13,290 --> 00:53:16,190
Gosh, don't treat me like
I'm a different person.

777
00:53:16,190 --> 00:53:17,780
It makes us feel so distant.

778
00:53:17,930 --> 00:53:20,560
Do you even know how
much I missed you guys?

779
00:53:20,560 --> 00:53:21,570
Really?

780
00:53:23,100 --> 00:53:25,190
- You missed us?
- Yes.

781
00:53:27,410 --> 00:53:29,830
I knew that I would've
left a hole in your heart.

782
00:53:29,940 --> 00:53:32,000
But hearing you actually say that
is making me blush a little.

783
00:53:33,270 --> 00:53:35,840
- You really haven't changed at all.
- No, I haven't.

784
00:53:37,710 --> 00:53:39,430
Is everyone else doing well?

785
00:53:40,910 --> 00:53:42,930
Mr. Choi and Ms. Dan...

786
00:53:43,250 --> 00:53:46,080
are busy these days. I think
they both started dating someone.

787
00:53:46,520 --> 00:53:49,380
And Mr. Lee is still very sensitive
and poetic as always.

788
00:53:52,730 --> 00:53:54,860
Is Mr. Kwon also doing well?

789
00:53:55,600 --> 00:53:56,780
No, not really.

790
00:53:57,410 --> 00:54:01,240
I feel anxious because it feels like
he'll get himself in trouble soon.

791
00:54:03,100 --> 00:54:06,910
I think he's going to
defend Park Su Myeong.

792
00:54:07,770 --> 00:54:11,380
What? Park Su Myeong?

793
00:54:25,120 --> 00:54:29,200
Mr. Kwon, are you doing well?

794
00:54:30,040 --> 00:54:33,540
I'm texting because I suddenly
got reminded of you...

795
00:54:52,430 --> 00:54:54,820
Do you remember me?

796
00:54:57,560 --> 00:54:58,880
Yes, I remember you.

797
00:54:59,230 --> 00:55:02,190
Your mother came to see me.

798
00:55:03,270 --> 00:55:04,950
She asked me to help you.

799
00:55:06,310 --> 00:55:09,160
So I'd appreciate it if you answer...

800
00:55:09,500 --> 00:55:12,070
the questions I'm about to ask you.

801
00:55:12,750 --> 00:55:14,870
Okay, I'll answer them.

802
00:55:15,140 --> 00:55:19,180
I heard you stabbed
Im Yun Hee's husband just once.

803
00:55:20,310 --> 00:55:21,320
Is that correct?

804
00:55:22,520 --> 00:55:25,690
Yes, I stabbed him once.

805
00:55:26,430 --> 00:55:28,690
He always beat her up.

806
00:55:28,690 --> 00:55:31,150
So I got really angry and stabbed him.

807
00:55:32,830 --> 00:55:34,730
Then Yun Hee told me to run away.

808
00:55:34,730 --> 00:55:37,660
I did what she told me to do and ran away.

809
00:55:41,230 --> 00:55:42,920
But where's my mom?

810
00:55:44,640 --> 00:55:46,090
My mom's suffering.

811
00:55:46,270 --> 00:55:47,960
I need to help her.

812
00:55:48,750 --> 00:55:50,540
I need to help my mom.

813
00:55:50,540 --> 00:55:52,060
I need to make deliveries.

814
00:55:52,410 --> 00:55:56,290
I don't... I don't want
my mom to suffer anymore.

815
00:55:57,620 --> 00:56:01,660
I really stabbed him just once. Only once.

816
00:56:02,500 --> 00:56:05,760
I only stabbed him once. Just once.

817
00:56:33,080 --> 00:56:34,510
Jung Rok, have you gone mad?

818
00:56:35,790 --> 00:56:39,100
You're actually going to
defend Park Su Myeong?

819
00:56:42,160 --> 00:56:43,170
Yes.

820
00:56:46,000 --> 00:56:49,440
Okay, I'll be really generous
and try to assume...

821
00:56:50,180 --> 00:56:52,300
that there could actually
be another culprit.

822
00:56:52,640 --> 00:56:53,910
But if that's true,
people will criticize you...

823
00:56:53,910 --> 00:56:55,090
for having made an innocent person guilty.

824
00:56:55,940 --> 00:56:59,120
On the other hand, if Park Su Myeong
turns out to be the culprit,

825
00:56:59,890 --> 00:57:01,070
you'll still get criticized...

826
00:57:01,160 --> 00:57:03,580
for trying to defend him at this point...

827
00:57:04,350 --> 00:57:06,810
when you've already accused him of murder.

828
00:57:07,930 --> 00:57:10,890
They'll question why you're being
so wishy-washy about the case.

829
00:57:11,390 --> 00:57:12,510
People will lose...

830
00:57:13,370 --> 00:57:15,890
their trust for you as an attorney.

831
00:57:15,960 --> 00:57:17,480
I've already decided to defend him.

832
00:57:19,040 --> 00:57:20,850
I even filed a copy of the
POA at the courthouse.

833
00:57:21,500 --> 00:57:22,510
What?

834
00:57:25,270 --> 00:57:27,090
- I'm sorry.
- You're sorry?

835
